Locality: Along edge of Lilac hedge under a small tree, nearby work trail in park.
Comments: I was sent out to cut and chemically treat this known patch of invasive Barberry in Crow-Hassan Park Reserve, though at that time, I was told it was Japanese Barberry (Berberis thunbergii).  I completed that task on 9/24/2012.  I was later sent back to that site for a follow-up on 7/1/2013 and found a few stems that had been initially missed.  After having worked with a few other patches of Japanese Barberry, I knew something didn't look right.  I took pictures of the missed stem and hunted and found seedlings growing nearby and took photo vouchers of their germination.  I cut and treated the missed stems and pulled all seedlings I could find.  Later that year, identified this plant as Common Barberry (Berberis vulgaris) and didn't think to post it until today.
